  "prompt": "My mom makes me eat less than my BMR for weight loss. what should I do?",
  "response": "If your mother is making you eat less than your Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR), this could be harmful to your health. Here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. Educate yourself\n- Learn about healthy nutrition and weight loss\n- Understand that eating below BMR can be dangerous\n\n2. Talk to your mother\n- Explain your concerns about potential health risks\n- Show her reliable information about proper nutrition\n- Ask to involve a healthcare professional\n\n3. Seek professional help\n- Consult a doctor or registered dietitian\n- Get personalized advice about healthy weight management\n- Have a professional discuss nutrition with your mother\n\n4. Potential health risks of eating below BMR\n- Slowed metabolism\n- Muscle loss\n- Nutritional deficiencies\n- Weakened immune system\n- Potential eating disorder development\n\n5. If you feel unsafe or pressured\n- Talk to a school counselor\n- Discuss the situation with a trusted adult\n- Seek support from other family members\n\nRemember: Healthy weight loss involves balanced nutrition and gradual, sustainable changes. Your health and well-being are important.\n\nWould you like help finding resources about healthy nutrition?",
